    Multi-file ZIP Resources

    multifile_zip_resources.Rmd

    When a resource is a ZIP file containing multiple files, the result is a named list. For example, the dataset on the Annual Summary of Reportable Communicable Diseases:

    library(opendatatoronto)

summary_diseases <- search_packages("Annual Summary of Reportable Communicable Diseases") %>%
  list_package_resources() %>%
  get_resource()

    To access a single file, you can pull out the element by name:

    summary_diseases[["RatesbyDisease2007_2017.csv"]]
#> NULL
